cs.NI, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.CR, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper is about a network programming language for software-defined networking.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper presents a new programming language.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper discusses the equivalence problem and decidability of certain problems related to the language.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions quality-of-service and fairness aspects, which can be related to security and privacy concerns.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the generalization of network functions and service chains, which can involve data structures and algorithms.
